OL,3,C'The village died... never recovered':
OL,4,CWhy the miners' strike still matters
OL,6,F"You've only got to look around this
OL,7,Froom now," says Ken Burkhill. "It's
OL,8,Fbristling with history isn't it? It's
OL,9,Femotional just being in here and
OL,10,Fthinking of the people that have stood
OL,11,Fon that stage and the speeches that
OL,12,Fhave been made."
OL,14,FAlmost 40 years on from the first days
OL,15,Fof the miners' strike, we are sitting
OL,16,Fin the headquarters of the National
OL,17,FUnion of Mineworkers (NUM).
