OL,3,C'The village died... never recovered':
OL,4,CWhy the miners' strike still matters
OL,6,FThe walls are covered by the
OL,7,Fintricate, colourful union banners of
OL,8,Fpits which have long since disappeared
OL,9,Ffrom view.
OL,11,FBut for Ken ` a miner at Maltby Main
OL,12,FColliery for 23 years ` the conviction
OL,13,Fthat sustained him and tens of
OL,14,Fthousands of miners during the bitter
OL,15,Fand costly 12-month-long dispute is as
OL,16,Fstrong today as it was in 1984.
OL,18,FAs is the enmity towards the
OL,19,FConservative government of the time -
OL,20,Fand most especially Margaret Thatcher.
