OL,3,C'The village died... never recovered':
OL,4,CWhy the miners' strike still matters
OL,6,F"There was only ever one union they
OL,7,Fwere coming for and that was us," he
OL,8,Fsays. "Make no bones about it, they
OL,9,Fset their stall out to ambush the
OL,10,Fminers and that's what happened from
OL,11,F1984 onwards. She (Margaret Thatcher)
OL,12,Fwanted revenge."
OL,14,FRevenge, he says, for the miners'
OL,15,Fstrike of ten years before - which
OL,16,Fbrought down Ted Heath's government in
OL,17,F1974.
