OL,3,C'The village died... never recovered':
OL,4,CWhy the miners' strike still matters
OL,6,FKen, his lifelong friend and fellow
OL,7,FMaltby miner Mick Connole, and John
OL,8,FDunn - who worked at Glapwell and
OL,9,FMarkham collieries - have come here to
OL,10,Ftalk to me about their memories and
OL,11,Fexperiences of the 1984 strike, but
OL,12,Fthey're keen I understand where the
OL,13,Froots of the conflict began.
OL,15,FAll three speak of the Ridley Plan - a
OL,16,Freport drawn up in the aftermath of
OL,17,FHeath's defeat which set out how the
OL,18,Fnext Conservative government could
OL,19,Ffight - and defeat - a major strike in
OL,20,Fa nationalised industry.
