OL,3,C'The village died... never recovered':
OL,4,CWhy the miners' strike still matters
OL,6,F"They knew, they had everything
OL,7,Fplanned but I think that our
OL,8,Fresilience and our strength surprised
OL,9,Fthem," says John.
OL,11,FResilience and strength are apposite
OL,12,Fwords for all three men. They are
OL,13,Fstill fiercely proud of their heritage
OL,14,Fand fiercely political about the
OL,15,Fconsequences of its demise. Mick
OL,16,Freflects sadly on the loss of
OL,17,Fcommunity, the pockets of deprivation
OL,18,Fand poverty left behind.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G5/13
