OL,3,C'The village died... never recovered':
OL,4,CWhy the miners' strike still matters
OL,6,F"In every village, anywhere, people
OL,7,Fwalked to work. You had your feeder
OL,8,Findustries - brickyards, clothing
OL,9,Ffactories, distribution businesses in
OL,10,Fevery village. It all went. Every one.
OL,11,FPeople had money in their pockets,
OL,12,Fthere were none of these deprived
OL,13,Fareas. Everyone had jobs and it just
OL,14,Fwent, almost overnight," he says.
