OL,3,C'The village died... never recovered':
OL,4,CWhy the miners' strike still matters
OL,6,F"They closed the mine and the village
OL,7,Fdied. Never recovered, just
OL,8,Fabandoned," adds John. "We haven't got
OL,9,Fany major industries any more. When
OL,10,Fpeople look at the insecure future
OL,11,Fthey face, it's as a consequence of
OL,12,Fwhat happened to us. As the timeline
OL,13,Ffrom 1984 is followed through, we
OL,14,Fwouldn't be in this mess if the
OL,15,Foutcome of our strike had been
OL,16,Fdifferent."
