OL,3,C'The village died... never recovered':
OL,4,CWhy the miners' strike still matters
OL,6,FSome wanted to fight because they knew
OL,7,Fin the long run they were going to
OL,8,Flose their jobs. Other people said
OL,9,Fit's a democratic vote, we've voted to
OL,10,Fwork, we're going to work. I'm pretty
OL,11,Fmuch in the middle really, I can see
OL,12,Fboth sides and I understand that", he
OL,13,Ftells me. "If we'd had a national
OL,14,Fballot and had a 'no' vote, we'd have
OL,15,Flost maybe one pit. But if we'd have
OL,16,Fhad that, we would have kept everyone
OL,17,Funited. 'The miners united will never
OL,18,Fbe defeated' we kept chanting. But we
OL,19,Fweren't united were we? That was the
OL,20,Fproblem."
