OL,3,C'The village died... never recovered':
OL,4,CWhy the miners' strike still matters
OL,6,FAnd Graham holds Arthur Scargill
OL,7,Fresponsible for that division. "You
OL,8,Fdon't divide and conquer your own
OL,9,Ftroops do you? You're supposed to
OL,10,Fdivide and conquer your enemy but we
OL,11,Fhanded it to them on a plate. We were
OL,12,Ffighting for our livelihoods and we
OL,13,Fended up fighting each other."
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G10/13
