OL,3,C'The village died... never recovered':
OL,4,CWhy the miners' strike still matters
OL,6,FThat such opposing views are still
OL,7,Fheld 40 years later demonstrates just
OL,8,Fhow deeply the miners' strike cut into
OL,9,Fthe heart of the industrial, economic
OL,10,Fand social landscape not only of
OL,11,FYorkshire, but the nation. A defining
OL,12,Fmoment of the twentieth century and in
OL,13,Fthe lives of those who were there. One
OL,14,Fwhich Ken, Mick and John are
OL,15,Fdetermined will never be forgotten.
OL,17,F"It was my most noble year, the most
OL,18,Fnoble thing I've done," says Mick.
OL,20,F"I would proudly say it was the best
OL,21,Fyear of my life," adds John.
