OL,3,C'The village died... never recovered':
OL,4,CWhy the miners' strike still matters
OL,6,FWhy does it matter now, I ask, when
OL,7,Fmining has long been consigned to the
OL,8,Fpast?
OL,10,F"Everyone in Yorkshire should be proud
OL,11,Fof the fact that the miners took them
OL,12,Fon and fought," Ken replies. "Future
OL,13,Fgenerations have got to look back in
OL,14,Fhistory and learn from mistakes. It's
OL,15,Fbeen hard this last 40 years but while
OL,16,Fever we've still go breath in our
OL,17,Fbody, we'll keep telling them to
OL,18,Ffight. Because if you don't fight
OL,19,Fyou'll never win anything."
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G12/13
